High-Fidelity Prototype Specification: MyLocalHub
1. General InformationThe prototype is a multi-file web application (SPA interface using vanilla JS) designed to simulate a mobile-first experience.
 The primary focus is on visual identity, interface warmth, and user retention mechanisms.

Language Requirement: All user interface elements, mock data, console logs, and code comments must be written strictly in English.
2. Visual Strategy and PaletteThe design aims to evoke a sense of trust and local belonging.
Color Scheme:Background: #FAF7F3 (Off-white/Parchment) — A warm background to reduce eye strain.
Primary Text: #2B2B2B (Graphite) — Soft black for high legibility.
Metadata/Secondary: #AAAAAA (Silver) — For supporting information (opening hours, distance).
Primary Accent: #C65A3A (Rosy Copper) — The main color for buttons and primary actions, associated with terracotta and craftsmanship.
Secondary Accent: #2F6F6D (Teal) — Represents calmness and the sea (connection to Larnaca), used for contrast.
Rewards/Gold: #F2C94C (Tuscan Sun) — For achievement indicators and loyalty points.
Typography: SF Pro font family (or an equivalent humanist sans-serif).
 Headings should be Bold, while body text is Regular.
Graphics: Corner radius — 16px.
 Icons — Thin, rounded line icons.
 Use real photos instead of stock imagery to enhance authenticity.
3.
 Screen Architecture3.
1.
 Explore (Home)Header: Greeting "Hello, [User Name]!" and a search bar.
Categories: Horizontal scroll (Food & Drink, Crafts, Beauty, Leisure).
Shop Cards: Cards featuring a photo, rating, and a mandatory promotion tag (e.
g.
, "BOGO" or "-30%").
Social Proof: Text below cards such as "120 people visited this week".
3.
2.
 Shop DetailHero Section: High-quality photo of the shop (e.
g.
, Georgios' Seaside Kiosk).
Promo Block: An accented section in Rosy Copper color describing the current offer.
Interaction: Primary buttons for "View Shop" and "Join Event".
3.
3.
 EventsList: Cards for upcoming community activities (craft fairs, workshops).
Style: Teal-themed design to distinguish events from commercial offers.
3.
4.
 Rewards (Loyalty)Points View: A large gold widget displaying the current point balance.
Progress: A progress bar with text like "You're close to a free coffee!".
QR Access: A button to trigger a modal window with a QR code for in-store scanning.
3.
5.
 ProfileImpact: A reflective block stating "You've supported 12 local businesses this month".
Badges: A grid of earned achievements ("Local Hero", "Explorer").
4.
 Emotional and Persuasive Interaction (HCI)Positive Feedback: Trigger a short confetti animation upon earning points or claiming a reward.
UI Language: Friendly and engaging tone.
 Use "Thank you for supporting local!" instead of generic "Operation complete".
Persuasion: Implement "Streaks" (consecutive visit days) and "Your reward expires soon" notifications.
Reflective Level: Monthly impact summaries to foster a sense of pride and community contribution.
5.
 Technical Project Structureindex.
html: App container, includes Bootstrap 5 and Google Fonts.
css/style.
css: Custom CSS variables for the palette and card styling.
js/app.
js: Main navigation controller (SPA) and component rendering logic.
js/mocks/:shops.
js: Data for businesses (including Georgios' kiosk).
events.
js: List of community events.
user.
js: User state (points, history, badges).
